BFN 

<F P=106> ["Communique" issued by the Shaanxi Provincial Statistics </F>
Bureau on 24 February 1993: "Statistical Report Issued by the 
Shaanxi Provincial Statistics Bureau on National Economic and 
Social Development in 1993"] 
  [Text] In 1993, under the leadership of the Shaanxi 
Provincial CPC Committee and Government, all the people of 
Shaanxi comprehensively implemented the guidelines of the 14th 
CPC National Congress and the Third Plenary of the 14th CPC 
Central Committee, quickened the pace of reform, opening up, and 
economic construction, and achieved obvious results in improving 
the macroenvironment and strengthening macroregulation and 
control. The national economy of the whole province grew 
rapidly, various social undertakings developed further, the 
living standards of the people were further improved, and a 
solid foundation was laid for further deepening reform, opening 
wider to the outside world, and the sustained, rapid, and 
healthy development [chi xu kuai su jian kang fa zhan 2170 4958 
1816 6643 0256 1660 4099 1455] of the national economy 
throughout the whole province in 1994. According to preliminary 
statistics, the domestic gross output value for the year was 
60.34 billion yuan, 12 percent up from the previous year, of 
which the added value of primary industry was 13.58 billion 
yuan, an increase of 9.6 percent; the added value of secondary 
industry was 29.12 billion yuan, an increase of 17.3 percent; 
and the added value of tertiary industry was 17.64 billion yuan, 
an increase of 5.3 percent. The major problems in economic 
operations were: The situation regarding poor economic results 
has not yet been fundamentally changed; prices rose too fast and 
the pressure of inflation increased; financial resources were 
insufficient and the shortage of funds was quite conspicuous; 
and constraining factors in basic industries and infrastructure 
increased and this was not in keeping with the needs of the 
economic and social development. 
<H5>  I. Agriculture </H5>
  In 1993, governments at all levels resolutely implemented a 
series of measures to strengthen agriculture and rural work 
adopted by the central authorities, reduced peasants' burden, 
increased input into agriculture, continued to readjust the 
production structure in rural areas, made great efforts to carry 
out construction of water conservancy works, and reaped 
unprecedented bumper harvests in agricultural production. The 
added value of agriculture for the whole year was 13.58 billion 
yuan, 9.6 percent over the previous year. 
  Relatively great progress was made in readjusting the 
production structure of agriculture and the percentage of 
high-quality, high-output, high-added-value products increased. 
The output of grain, edible oils, and fruit increased by a big 
margin, reaching a record high. Because of the reduced growing 
area and serious natural disasters, the output of cotton and 
cured tobacco was less than in the previous year. The output of 
major agricultural produce was as follows: 


