  The industrial economic results comprehensive index was 71.6 
percent, 1.1 percentage points higher than the previous year, of 
which the product marketing rate was 95.68 percent, the profit 
and tax rate of funds was 6.54 percent, the profit rate of costs 
and spending was 2.20 percent, the turnover rate of current 
assets was 1.26 times, the rate of added value of industry was 
29.9 percent, and the all-personnel labor productivity 
(calculated in terms of added value) was 8,925 yuan per person. 
  The building industry developed quite quickly, the quality 
of construction was raised, and the economic results improved. 
In 1993, with the growth of investment in fixed assets and the 
deepening reform of the building industry, the construction rate 
was quickened. Construction enterprises attained 4.8 billion 
yuan's worth of added value, 9.4 percent up. The economic 
results in state-owned building and construction enterprises 
comprehensively increased once again and the all-personnel labor 
productivity was 29,462 yuan, 76.9 percent up. The percentage 
of money-losing enterprises decreased from 18.1 to 16.9 percent. 
Profits obtained by enterprises also increased to a certain 
extent. With the increase in construction tasks, the quality of 
construction products also increased. The good quality rate of 
unit project in acceptance assessment rose from 52.0 to 65.5 
percent. 
  New progress was made in general geological surveys and 
prospecting. In 1993, the geologically prospecting system 
completed 13,000 m of mechanical core drilling. Mineral 
deposits were discovered in four new places, 38 geological 
reports of various kinds were submitted, and more deposits of 
four kinds of minerals were proven. 
<H5>  III. Investment in Fixed Assets </H5>
  The range of increase in investment in fixed assets was 
quite 
wide. The investment in fixed assets by the whole society 
amounted to 21.5 billion yuan, 50.9 percent up, of which 
investment made by state-owned units amounted to 17.3 billion 
yuan, an increase of 67.3 percent; investment made by collective 
organizations amounted to 1.2 billion yuan, an increase of 58.1 
percent; and investment made by urban and rural residents 
amounted to 3 billion yuan, an increase of 14.5 percent. 
  In the investment by state-owned units, investment in 
capital 
construction amounted to 10.1 billion yuan, 63.8 percent up; 
investment in renovation and transformation amounted to 5.6 
billion yuan, an increase of 73.3 percent; and investment in 
other fixed assets amounted to 1.6 billion yuan, an increase of 
69.1 percent. 
  The investment structure was readjusted to a certain extent 
and the basic industries and tertiary industry were 
strengthened. Of investment made by state-owned units, the 
percentage used in the renovation and transformation of 
enterprises and institutions rose from 31.7 to 35.7 percent, the 
percentage used in intensive [nei han di 0355 3211 4104] 
expansion of reproduction, improving quality of products, 
increasing varieties, and reducing energy consumption rose from 
30.8 to 32.0 percent; and the percentage used in the extensive 
[wai han di 1120 3211 4104] expansion of reproduction and 
increasing output dropped from 26.7 to 23.6 percent. In terms 
of trade, state-owned units mainly made investment in the basic 
industries and infrastructure. Investment in raw material 
industries increased by 74.6 percent; in the power industry, by 
49.8 percent; transportation, postal services, and 
telecommunications, by 97.3 percent; and agriculture decreased 
by 10.4 percent. In terms of the industrial structure, the 
percentage of investment in the tertiary industry rose from 33.9 
to 38.6 percent. 
  The speed of construction in the "project to revitalize 
Shaanxi" and in other key projects was accelerated. In 
implementing the policy of the central authorities to improve 
and strengthen macroregulation and control, the provincial 
leadership prioritized the 38 items in the implementation of the 
"project to revitalize Shaanxi" in 1993 and accelerated the 
construction progress of 22 items. The Shaanxi Historical 
Museum and the Yaoxian County Cement Plant were accepted by the 
state. Rails were laid in the 115 km section within Shaanxi of 
the Baoji-Zhongwei Railroad and the section of the Xian-Baoji 
Highway from Xian to Xingping was opened to traffic. The Weihe 
Power Plant No. 5 Generating Unit entered the installation 
stage, laying a foundation for putting the unit into operation 
in 1994. Two generating sets in the Hengshan Power Plant began 
supplying electricity to the power grid. A special railroad 
line for the Weihe Chemical Fertilizer Plant was put into 
operation and the construction of major production projects at 
the plant was started in a comprehensive manner. The 
construction of the telecommunications fiber-optic cables from 
Xian to Chengdu, from Xian to Zhengzhou, and from Xian to Yanan, 
were completed and put into operation. The capital construction 
for the production of the Aotuo mini-sedan cars and the 
renovation and transformation of equipment for the production of 
such cars were completed. The installation of equipment in two 
major workshops in the project for the production of diacetic 
acid fiber yarn began. The construction and installation work 
at the Huangling Mineral Zone Ore Dressing Plant was completed 
ahead of schedule and the commissioning stage began. Trial 
production of the Yulin Natural Gas Chemical Works began. Pipes 
were laid to transfer water from Xian's Hei He to the urban 
areas. 
<H5>  IV. Transportation, Postal and Telecommunications Services </H5>
  Transportation, postal and telecommunications services 
continued to develop steadily. The added value of 
transportation, postal and telecommunications services amounted 
to 5.2 billion yuan, 10.4 percent up, and its percentage in the 
domestic gross output value rose from 6.1 to 8.6 percent. 
However, the "bottleneck" restraint transportation causes in 
economic development was still very obvious. Although 
production of railway transportation was carefully organized, 
the shortage in transportation capacity has not yet eased. The 
sufficiency rate for rolling stock was 60 percent. The structure 
of highway transportation was quite irrational and this affected 
the utilization of the transportation capacity and the 
improvement of economic results. 



